with the water. Living in an African Country, I have been insulated from the water problem to some extent. But not anymore.
I hear many Home products designed for use in developing countries which solve their problem with water. Eg. Give it to Me Water Filter, the Lily Light, SolarVego Water Sanitation, Invisible House Water Purification and Ranking Fuel Tank. Maybe the problem is solved but the consumer does not care?
How can I convince my Audience that they should care?
Why should I?
Okay, we will not be rid of the water problems by my generation. I think this will take eons. We will only make strides towards it.
Getting our Population Southwest Texas Python Clearing to Change Their Mind and Actively Involve Themselves in the Challenge is the first step. When they become of age and start having families themselves, I expect that something that is Familiar during their generation will be thrust into a much greater involvement in the problem. I foresee many Generation XBabyBoomers leading programs for developing countries. Their lovechild, Generation Y will propel things further and provide a platform of cooler technology making the problems more seamless to the eyes.
